                                al-muta&#x1E6D;abbib, except that he must have worked between the time of
                                    <name type="person">Ibn al-Tilm&#x12B;dh</name>(d. 549/1154 or
                                560/1165) and 1593, when the copy was completed. It is stated in the
                                manuscript that it was compiled by &#x1E62;af&#x12B; al-Dawlah M&#x101;lik ibn Ab&#x12B;
                                al-Najm al-Mas&#x12B;&#x1E25;&#x12B; from extracts taken from the Aqr&#x101;b&#x101;dh&#x12B;n by Ibn
                                al-Tilm&#x12B;dh. Despite its apparent derivative nature, however, this
                                treatise is quite different from the Aqr&#x101;b&#x101;dh&#x12B;n of Ibn
                                al-Tilm&#x12B;dh.</note>
